<paragraph id="8BE4BD5F1D102B495E50F93374C0566C" blockId="13.[828,1479,1728,1880]" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D102B495E50F933736B57EC" box="[874,1143,1728,1752]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName id="4C5BC6DC1D102B4959A0F933724557EC" box="[1178,1369,1728,1752]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="13" pageNumber="336" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D102B4959A0F933724557EC" box="[1178,1369,1728,1752]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Benstonea ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed from Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="F34CFDCF1D102B495912F913739057CC" box="[1064,1164,1760,1784]" name="Malaysia" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
to Borneo (through Sumatra and 
<collectingCountry id="F34CFDCF1D102B495E53F8F374CA562C" box="[873,982,1792,1816]" name="Singapore" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Singapore</collectingCountry>
) and 
<collectingCountry id="F34CFDCF1D102B49592AF8F3736E562C" box="[1040,1138,1792,1816]" name="Thailand" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Thailand</collectingCountry>
. It grows in forest understory on hilltops, often on poor soils, at an altitude of 
<quantity id="4CA310BA1D102B49581CF8D372DF560C" box="[1318,1475,1824,1848]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.25" metricValueMax="13.5" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="13" pageNumber="336" unit="m" value="825.0" valueMax="1350.0" valueMin="300.0">300 to 1350 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFCAC0AE1D102B495E7FF8B374D3566C" author="STONE, B. C." box="[837,975,1856,1880]" pageId="13" pageNumber="336" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16436" refString="STONE, B. C. (1978). Revisio Pandanacearum, Part I. Pandanus subgenera Coronata and Acrostigma. Flora Malesiana precursores. Fed. Mus. J. 23: 1 - 74." type="journal article" year="1978">STONE, 1978</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4BD5F1D132B4A5D99FEEA755D5225" blockId="14.[118,773,281,1080]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5D99FEEA76335005" box="[163,303,281,305]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Observations</emphasis>
. – 
<taxonomicName id="4C5BC6DC1D132B4A5C6AFEEA750C5005" box="[336,528,281,305]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5C6AFEEA750C5005" box="[336,528,281,305]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Pandanus ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCAC0AE1D132B4A5D4CFECA76505065" author="GAUDICHAUD, C." box="[118,332,313,337]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" refId="ref15083" refString="GAUDICHAUD, C. (1841). Voyage autour du mondeexecutependant les annees 1836 - 1837 sur lacorvette &quot; LaBonite &quot; comandee par M. Vaillant. Botanique. Atlas. Arthus Bertrand, Paris." type="book" year="1841">GAUDICHAUD (1841)</bibRefCitation>
in the invalidely published genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5BC6DC1D132B4A5F8BFECA76365045" authority="Gaudich. This" authorityName="Gaudich. This" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Fisquetia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5F8BFECA778D5045" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Fisquetia</emphasis>
Gaudich. This
</taxonomicName>
name was then invalidly transferred by KURZ (1869) to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5BC6DC1D132B4A5DDAFE8A765050A5" box="[224,332,377,401]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5DDAFE8A765050A5" box="[224,332,377,401]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Pandanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, without a description. SOLMS- 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCAC0AE1D132B4A5FA3FE8A77DC5085" author="LAUBACH, H." pageId="14" pageNumber="337" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref15861" refString="SOLMS- LAUBACH, H. (1878). Monographia Pandanacearum. Linnaea 42: 1 - 110." type="journal article" year="1878">LAUBACH (1878)</bibRefCitation>
, while attempting to transfer it to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5BC6DC1D132B4A5F04FE6A75B75085" box="[574,683,409,433]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5F04FE6A75B75085" box="[574,683,409,433]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Pandanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, in fact described it as new, designating 
<specimenCount id="9D5D76D61D132B4A5CEAFE4A757E50E5" box="[464,610,441,465]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
: Gaudichaud’s drawing and a 
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5C28FE2A768850C5" box="[274,404,473,497]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Gaudichaud</emphasis>
collection in the Delessert herbarium in G 
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5DE3FE0A76865325" box="[217,410,505,529]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">(Gaudichaud 108)</emphasis>
. His description thus validates the name as 
<taxonomicName id="4C5BC6DC1D132B4A5DF7FDEA76305305" box="[205,300,537,561]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornatus">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5DF7FDEA76305305" box="[205,300,537,561]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">P.ornatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, even though he believed he was simply making a new combination. 
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5C54FDCA75005365" box="[366,540,569,593]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Gaudichaud 108</emphasis>
has both an infructescence and leaves, and is here designated as the 
<typeStatus id="54E003FD1D132B4A5F5EFDAA75DB5345" box="[612,711,601,625]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">lectotype</typeStatus>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C5BC6DC1D132B4A5FF4FDAA761253A5" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5FF4FDAA761253A5" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Benstonea ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by a sub-cylindric cephalia (varying in length from 
<quantity id="4CA310BA1D132B4A5C4BFD6A76F95385" box="[369,485,665,689]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" unit="cm" value="14.0" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="5.0">5 to 23 cm</quantity>
), pendent on a long peduncle (up to 
<quantity id="4CA310BA1D132B4A5DD8FD4A763A53E5" box="[226,294,697,721]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" unit="cm" value="50.0">50 cm</quantity>
) with sharp, proximally arcuate styles up to 
<quantity id="4CA310BA1D132B4A5D4CFD2A77AE53C5" box="[118,178,729,753]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 mm</quantity>
in length (
<figureCitation id="1360A1DA1D132B4A5C1AFD2A766D53C5" box="[288,369,729,753]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[118,143,1873,1893]" captionTargetBox="[118,1494,265,1835]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. – Infructescences and details of stigmas of species of Benstonea Callm. &amp; Buerki. A. Benstonea affinis (Kurz) Callm. &amp; Buerki; B. Benstonea gibbsiana (Martelli) Callm. &amp; Buerki; C. Benstonea ornata (Solms) Callm. &amp; Buerki; D. Benstonea pachyphylla (Merr.) Callm. &amp; Buerki. [Photos: M. W. Callmander]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5799762" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5799762/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). This species is wonderfully illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCAC0AE1D132B4A5DABFD0A767F5225" author="GAUDICHAUD, C." box="[145,355,761,785]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" refId="ref15083" refString="GAUDICHAUD, C. (1841). Voyage autour du mondeexecutependant les annees 1836 - 1837 sur lacorvette &quot; LaBonite &quot; comandee par M. Vaillant. Botanique. Atlas. Arthus Bertrand, Paris." type="book" year="1841">GAUDICHAUD (1841</bibRefCitation>
: Tab. 5, 
<figureCitation id="1360A1DA1D132B4A5C81FD0A751D5225" box="[443,513,761,785]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[118,144,1874,1894]" captionTargetBox="[118,1494,267,1835]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. – General habit, infructescences and details of stigmas of species of Pandanus sect. Epiphytica Martelli (A-B) and Pseudoacrostigma B. C. Stone (C-D). A-B. Pandanus epiphyticus Martelli; C. Pandanus platystigma Martelli; D. Pandanus pugnax B. C. Stone. [Photos: M. W. Callmander]" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5790004" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5790004/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Figs. 1</figureCitation>
, 8-9).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE4BD5F1D132B4A5D99FCD376DF550C" blockId="14.[118,773,281,1080]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">
<bibRefCitation id="EFCAC0AE1D132B4A5D99FCD37641520C" author="MARTELLI, U." box="[163,349,800,824]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" pagination="298 - 304" refId="ref15762" refString="MARTELLI, U. (1904). Pandani asiatici nuovi. Bull. Soc. Bot. Ital. 1904: 298 - 304." type="journal article" year="1904">MARTELLI (1904)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="4C5BC6DC1D132B4A5CE9FCD375A7520C" box="[467,699,800,824]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monotheca">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5CE9FCD375A7520C" box="[467,699,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Pandanus monotheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on 
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5DA0FCB37629526C" box="[154,309,832,856]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Ridley 10821.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="54E003FD1D132B4A5C4BFCB376CE526C" box="[369,466,832,856]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">holotype</typeStatus>
deposited at CAL was not found by Stone, neither in 1968 nor in 1974 (STONE, 1978), and this entity was therefore regarded by him as a poorly known species. Drupes of this collection (with neither leaves nor syncarps) were, however, subsequently found in both FI and G. The FI collection, here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54E003FD1D132B4A5F71FC1375B252CC" box="[587,686,992,1016]" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">lectotype</typeStatus>
, clearly belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="4C5BC6DC1D132B4A5DCBFBF376AA552C" box="[241,438,1024,1048]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Benstonea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ornata">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5DCBFBF376AA552C" box="[241,438,1024,1048]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Benstonea ornata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5BC6DC1D132B4A5CCCFBF375F9552C" box="[502,741,1024,1048]" class="Liliopsida" family="Pandanaceae" genus="Pandanus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pandanales" pageId="14" pageNumber="337" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="monotheca">
<emphasis id="B92F614D1D132B4A5CCCFBF375F9552C" box="[502,741,1024,1048]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="337">Pandanus monotheca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is therefore treated as a synonym.
</paragraph>
